column2: Overcast day.  Temperature is in the mid-40s.

column1: Sunny and windy- water fairly clear
High scattered clouds.  Lake greening up and very weedy.

column2: Mostly sunny.  Greened up terribly in last week due to HOT temps-more coming
Hot- humid- sunny  Not quite as green as last week
Short window of blue sky.  Low wind has green scum on surface over entire area.

column1: Water has cleared up yet again.  Very Nice to see bottom at 8-10'

column2: Weed growth has nearly reached the surface.  Water clarity still very good.

column1: First flakes of algae appeared 6/18.  By 6/20 had greened up considerably.  Curly leaf pond weed and native "grass" weeds extensive to 12' most areas.

column2: CLear day.  Lake greened up but not as bad as last year.  Midge hatch 2 weeks later than usual--as everything seems to be this year--after 2 week later ice-out.

column1: Ice out April 13- But 80% out on April 11

column2: Starting to green up but nothing floating on top yet.

column1: Haven't had hot weather so growth is slow.

column2: Midge hatch just starting.  2 weeks later than usual as is everything else this year.

column1: Algae bloom started in earnest August 10.  Drastic drop in water clarity.

column2: Algae getting worse but is not laying on top of water as in past.
Curly leaf nearing surface out to 11' depth.
Curly Leaf at surface in several bays
Too cloudy on sunday for sat pass
Storms early in the week.  Heavy clouds for SAT pass monday.
First SAT day all month with clear sky.

column1: Cloudy after days of rain and wind had riled up the water.

column2: Several days of clear- sunny skies cleared the water up greatly.

column1: Adult loon with 2 large chicks between the islands
One of 2 loon chicks previously observed was taken by an eagle. (reported by Thomas Resort owner)

column2: Mayfly hatch started.  Late due to cool weather earlier with lack of green-until now.

column1: Saw young loon 1/2 grown diving w/parent.

column2: High winds may have dispersed the algae as reading was much better than expected.  Fridays sat pass had heavy clouds.

column1: 2 Young of the year loons seen fending for themselves.  Adults may be gone.

column2: Substantial blue-green algae bloom on west shore surface in the last mile of south end of lake.  Extremely bad smell.  Lack of wind for last week seems to have allowed it to surface.  Had been observed on east side of lake previously.

column1: First loon heard 3/26- but we were gone previous week
Low secchi reading perhaps due to prolonged high winds
7.2" rain in May w/4.5" last weekend.  High water.

column2: Day before Satellite-clear skies.  6/26 sat day overcast after 1pm

column1: Saw first loon chick with parents by island.

column2: Clear 'til noon- t-storms noon to 3p- mostly clear after 3p

column1: No loons heard or seen.  Chicks are usually here until ice-in.  Perhaps none survived this year.  Only saw one chick w/parents all summer.
May be the last reading of the yr if next weekend is as predicted
Loons back 4/26--not happy!  Saw 6 loons 5/19 various places

column2: Murkyness is disappointing.  Usually 7-8' this early.

column1: Have found one loon nest so far.  Many loons on lake.

column2: Lake greening up quickly in last 4-5 days
Satellite day: Mostly clear sky- passing cumulus clouds

column1: Have not seen a loon chick all summer.  One observed nesting.

column2: Satellite day-mostly cloudy/rain until 2p- some broken overcast/clouds later.

column1: Orioles may 9- humming birds May 10- Groosbeak may 10

column2: Satellite day clear sky with some clouds late
Clear sky until 1430- then increasing heavy overcast
Mainly clear morning with afternoon increasing cumulus clouds.

column1: Loons heard April 5.  Seen several times including one today.
Found one loon nest Thomas bay

column2: Satellite day fri 6/19/2015 clear with clouds late afternoon
8/30/2015 satellite day cloudy to 11am then mostly clear/hazy

column1: Several dozen fish- mostly crappies- floating dead.  Maybe didn't survive release
